<file path="business/03_Champion_Program/Anti_Cheat_Rules.md">
# Anti-Cheat Rules

Champion Program has cash on the line, so we treat integrity seriously from cohort 1.

## Day-1 baseline rules

- **Photo deadline:** Day-1 progress photo must be uploaded by 11:59 PM of Day 1. Late photos = ineligible for Champion (still in cohort).
- **Photo metadata:** Phone EXIF metadata is preserved on upload. We check for date manipulation.
- **Weight and waist:** Submitted with a short selfie video showing the scale/measuring tape. Coach reviews 100% of Day-1 video evidence.

## Mid-cohort

- **Suspicious daily check-ins:** If a user submits 21 perfect check-ins on Day 21 (i.e. backfilling), it's flagged. Backfilled days don't count for Consistency score.
- **Coach's red flag:** Any coach can flag a user for suspected fabrication. Flagged users go through additional video review for Champion eligibility.

## Day-21 submission

- **Photo consistency:** Day-21 photo must match Day-1 lighting, framing, and clothing reasonably. We don't expect perfect studio match, but obvious lighting tricks are flagged.
- **Random verification:** Top 5 finalists get a 5-min Zoom call with founder to verify weight, waist, and reflect on their journey. This becomes content with permission.

## Disqualification protocol

If we find evidence of fabrication:
1. User is disqualified from Champion ranking
2. User is allowed to complete cohort with no public note
3. User receives a 50% refund as goodwill (we don't want to make enemies)
4. User is not invited to future cohorts
5. No public shaming — ever.

## What we do not do

- We do not require gym/clinic verification (too high friction for ₹999 cohort)
- We do not run body fat / DEXA tests (too expensive)
- We do not penalize natural variance (water weight, time-of-day weighing)

## What we do trust by default

- The vast majority of users are honest. The rules above are 95% deterrent and 5% enforcement.
- Coach's gut is usually right. If a coach flags someone after 21 days of daily interaction, take it seriously.

## Edge case: medication-driven weight loss

If a user is on weight-loss medication (GLP-1 etc.), they must disclose it on the assessment. Their Champion eligibility is **not removed**, but the Physical dimension is capped at 50% (15/30 max) so they don't out-compete habit-driven users. This rule is published transparently in the Champion rules.
</file>

<file path="business/03_Champion_Program/Champion_Format.md">
# Fitterverse Champion Program

> "Every cohort produces 3 Champions. They are the proof that this works."

The Champion Program is the single most important marketing asset Fitterverse owns. Every cohort generates 3 named, documented transformations that compound into a transformation library no competitor can copy.

---

## What it is

At the end of every 21-day cohort, the top 3 transformations are crowned **Fitterverse Champions** — Gold, Silver, Bronze.

It is **not** a "biggest weight loss" contest. It rewards transformation across four dimensions, with consistency weighted highest. This is intentional: we don't want to reward extreme behavior, we want to reward exactly what we sell — sustainable habit change.

---

## Eligibility

Anyone enrolled in a cohort is eligible if they:
1. Completed at least 18 of 21 daily check-ins
2. Submitted Day-1 and Day-21 weight, waist, and progress photo
3. Submitted a written reflection (the Champion Submission, see template)
4. Did not violate the cohort group rules
5. Opted in to public sharing of their story

Users who don't want their story public are still eligible for **silent recognition** (badge in app, no public post).

---

## Prize structure (locked-in v1)

| Rank | Cash prize | Free continuation | Recognition |
|---|---|---|---|
| Gold (1st) | ₹10,000 | Free seat in next cohort | Featured case study + Hall of Fame |
| Silver (2nd) | ₹5,000 | Free seat in next cohort | Featured case study + Hall of Fame |
| Bronze (3rd) | ₹2,500 | Free seat in next cohort | Featured case study + Hall of Fame |

Total prize pool per cohort: **₹17,500 cash + 3 free seats (≈ ₹3,000 retail value)**

No merch in v1. We add Fitterverse-branded items in v2 once the brand has weight.

---

## Bonus recognition (every cohort, no limit)

Beyond Top 3, we recognize three more categories. These get a public shoutout but no cash:

- **Most Consistent** — highest daily check-in score (zero missed)
- **Biggest Comeback** — biggest improvement after a tough week 1
- **Group MVP** — most encouraging cohort member (peer-voted)

This means up to 6 people get publicly celebrated each cohort. More celebration = more UGC = more inbound for next cohort.

---

## Why this works (strategic notes)

1. **Cash prize ≈ what one user paid.** ₹10K is meaningful but not break-the-budget — it's roughly the LTV of one strong customer.
2. **Free next cohort + champions stay in the community.** This means our most successful users keep coming back as alumni — they become unpaid peer coaches and content creators.
3. **3 winners + 3 bonus categories = 6 stories per cohort.** Run 12 cohorts in a year and you have 70+ documented transformations. Few Indian fitness brands can match that volume of named proof.
4. **Public stories drive next cohort enrolment.** We launch the next cohort the same week we announce winners — the FOMO cycle compounds.
5. **Judging on consistency (not pure weight loss) protects the brand.** No one ever gets a Champion title for crash dieting.

---

## Anti-gaming rules

- Day-1 photo must be timestamped and submitted within 24 hours of cohort start
- Day-21 photo must be in same lighting, similar clothing, similar pose to Day 1
- Weight and waist measurements: video-confirm in 1 random user per Top 5 (zoom call)
- Anyone caught fabricating measurements or photos is disqualified and removed from the cohort with a 50% refund
- Coaches can flag suspicious submissions; flagged submissions go to founder for final call

---

## How winners are decided

See `Judging_Rubric.md` for the full scoring system. Summary:

- 40% Consistency (check-in days, habit score)
- 30% Physical change (weight, waist, progress photo blind-judge)
- 15% Habit transformation (sleep, water, protein, steps)
- 15% Story quality (reflection writing, depth of insight)

Three judges:
1. Lead coach
2. Founder
3. One previous Champion (from cohort 2 onwards)

---

## Announcement & content engine

| Day | Action | Owner |
|---|---|---|
| Day 22 | All eligible users submit Champion entries | Coach |
| Day 23 | Three judges score independently; scores combined | Founder |
| Day 24 | Top 3 announced live on Instagram (15-min show) + email + cohort group | Marketing |
| Day 25 | Winner case study posts: 1 reel + 1 carousel + 1 blog post per Champion | Content |
| Day 26 | Champions DMed for follow-up content (90-second video case study) | Content |
| Day 27 | All Champions added to Hall of Fame on website | Tech |
| Day 28 | Next cohort enrolment opens, with Champions featured in ads | Marketing |

---

## What every Champion gets (deliverable checklist)

- [ ] ₹ prize transferred via UPI within 7 days
- [ ] Free-seat code for next cohort emailed
- [ ] Featured case study published on fitterverse.in/stories
- [ ] 1 Instagram reel (60–90 sec) + 1 carousel post
- [ ] 1 long-form blog post on their journey (SEO asset)
- [ ] Hall of Fame entry with quote
- [ ] Optional: branded "Fitterverse Champion — Cohort N" digital badge they can use on LinkedIn
- [ ] Invitation to join Champions Circle (private alumni group)

---

## Champions Circle (the long game)

Once we have 9 Champions (after cohort 3), we open a private alumni community.

Champions get:
- Free maintenance plan support
- First access to new programs
- Optional: paid micro-creator role for content (post-cohort 6, when budget allows)

This is how Fitterverse builds an unpaid evangelist army.
</file>

<file path="business/03_Champion_Program/Judging_Rubric.md">
# Champion Judging Rubric

Total score = 100 points. Top 3 by total score win.

---

## Dimension 1: Consistency (40 points)

The single biggest weight. We reward showing up, not extreme effort.

| Sub-metric | Points | How |
|---|---|---|
| Daily check-in count (out of 21) | 15 | (count / 21) × 15 |
| Workouts completed (out of 14 prescribed) | 10 | (count / 14) × 10 |
| Plate method days logged (out of 21) | 8 | (count / 21) × 8 |
| Sleep target hit (out of 21) | 7 | (count / 21) × 7 |

**Floor:** Anyone with < 18 check-ins is automatically ineligible.

---

## Dimension 2: Physical change (30 points)

Judged blind by 3 judges who see only Day-1 vs Day-21 photo, weight delta %, waist delta %.

| Sub-metric | Points | Method |
|---|---|---|
| Photo transformation (visible posture, definition, presence) | 12 | 3 judges score 0–4 each, average × 3 |
| Weight delta (% of starting) | 9 | 0.5% loss = 1pt, 1% = 3pt, 2% = 6pt, 3%+ = 9pt |
| Waist delta (cm) | 9 | 1 cm = 2pt, 2 cm = 4pt, 3 cm = 6pt, 5cm+ = 9pt |

**Important:** This dimension is capped at 30 points. Someone with 6 kg loss does not get more than someone with 3 kg loss + better consistency. We are not paying out for crash dieting.

---

## Dimension 3: Habit transformation (15 points)

Compared between Week 1 average and Week 3 average from their tracker.

| Sub-metric | Points | How |
|---|---|---|
| Steps improvement (avg/day W3 - W1) | 4 | +1k = 1pt, +2k = 2pt, +3k = 3pt, +4k+ = 4pt |
| Water improvement | 3 | +0.5L = 1pt, +1L = 2pt, +1.5L+ = 3pt |
| Protein meals/day improvement | 4 | +0.5 = 1pt, +1 = 2pt, +1.5+ = 4pt |
| Sleep regularity improvement | 4 | std-dev of bedtime improved by 30 min = 2pt, by 60 min = 4pt |

---

## Dimension 4: Story quality (15 points)

Judges read all submission reflections blind (names redacted).

| Criterion | Points |
|---|---|
| Specific, honest, particular (not generic) | 5 |
| Clear before-state and clear after-state | 4 |
| One concrete behavior change they can articulate | 3 |
| Sustainability mindset — not "I'm cured" but "I'm continuing" | 3 |

---

## Tie-breaker order

1. Higher Consistency score wins
2. Then higher Habit transformation score
3. Then earlier Day-1 photo submission timestamp
4. Then coach's qualitative judgment

---

## Judges' protocol

- All scoring is independent; judges do not see each other's scores
- All identifying info (name, photo before scoring) is hidden in dimensions 3 and 4
- Photos in dimension 2 are shown blind (no name, no caption)
- Combined score = sum of three judges, divided by 3
- Founder has final call only on disqualification (anti-cheat), not on rank

---

## Worked example

| User | Consistency (40) | Physical (30) | Habit (15) | Story (15) | **Total** |
|---|---|---|---|---|---|
| User A | 38 | 22 | 13 | 12 | **85** ← Gold |
| User B | 35 | 28 | 11 | 10 | **84** ← Silver |
| User C | 36 | 18 | 12 | 14 | **80** ← Bronze |
| User D | 30 | 26 | 9 | 9 | 74 |
| User E | 21 | 12 | 8 | 10 | 51 (eligible but low) |
| User F | 17 | — | — | — | INELIGIBLE (< 18 check-ins) |

Notice User B had the biggest physical change but lost Gold to User A who was more consistent. That is the right outcome for what Fitterverse stands for.
