<file path="business/06_Coach_Ops/Escalation_Protocols.md">
# Coach Escalation Protocols

When the coach hits something outside their authority, this doc says what to do.

---

## Tier 1 — Coach handles independently

- General nutrition guidance (within plate-method framework)
- Workout modifications (knee, back, time-constrained)
- Motivation, encouragement, group moderation
- Lifestyle adjustments (sleep, water, steps, eating out)
- Cohort group conflicts (warning, removal if needed)

## Tier 2 — Escalate to lead coach within 4 hours

- New injury during cohort
- Repeated late-night anxiety messages
- User asking detailed nutrition for medical condition (PCOS, thyroid, diabetes)
- User expressing concerning eating patterns (skipping meals deliberately, extreme restriction)
- Cohort group dispute coach can't resolve

**Action:** Tag lead coach in dashboard with "ESC2" and one-line context.

## Tier 3 — Escalate to founder within 1 hour

- Refund request
- Anti-cheat flag (suspected fabrication)
- User mentions suicidal thoughts, severe mental distress
- Pregnancy disclosure mid-cohort
- Major medical event (chest pain, fainting, hospitalization)
- Press / media / legal contact

**Action:** Direct WhatsApp to founder with full context. Founder responds within 1 hour.

## Tier 4 — Immediate emergency

- Active medical emergency described in messages
- Anything criminal or legal (harassment, threats)

**Action:**
1. If life-threatening medical: tell user to call emergency services immediately (108 in India). Do not delay with messaging.
2. Notify founder by phone call (not text).
3. Document everything in writing within 24 hours.

---

## Specific scripts

### User mentions suicidal thoughts or severe mental distress

Coach reply (within 30 min):

> [First name], I hear you. I'm not the right person to help with this — and I want to make sure you get the right support.
>
> Please reach out to one of these now:
> - iCall: 9152987821 (Mon–Sat, 8 AM–10 PM)
> - Vandrevala Foundation: 1860-2662-345 (24/7)
>
> I'll check in with you again in 6 hours. You're not alone in this.

Then: notify founder immediately. Pause cohort participation for that user (no daily reminders). Founder follows up in 24 hours.

### User reveals eating disorder history

Coach reply:

> Thank you for telling me. I want to be straight with you — Fitterverse is a habit-and-fitness program, not a clinical eating disorder support program.
>
> I'd like to offer a full refund and pause your participation in this cohort. We can discuss a lighter, non-weight-focused version of the program, but only with sign-off from a qualified therapist or doctor.
>
> What feels right to you?

Then: escalate Tier 3.

### User reveals pregnancy mid-cohort

Coach reply:

> Congratulations. We're going to pause your participation here — Fitterverse v1 isn't designed for prenatal fitness, and I don't want to give you advice that's outside my training.
>
> We'll refund the unused portion. When you're ready postpartum, we have a separate program in development — I'll keep you on the waitlist.

Then: escalate Tier 3 + add to postpartum waitlist.

### User asks for refund

Day 1–3: Full refund, no questions.
Day 4–7: 50% refund.
Day 8+: No refund (per published policy), but we honor compelling cases at founder's discretion.

Coach script:
> I hear you. Per our refund policy, [X]. I've forwarded this to [founder name] and they'll follow up within 24 hours.

Then: escalate Tier 3 with one-line user context.

### User asks for medical specifics (e.g. PCOS diet plan)

Coach reply:
> That's a doctor-and-dietitian question, and I'm trained to do habit coaching, not medical nutrition therapy.
>
> What I can do: keep your habit floor steady (water, walks, protein, sleep, plate method). Whatever your doctor or dietitian says, I'll work around it.
>
> Want me to introduce you to a registered dietitian who works with us? (Available in Plus plan post-cohort.)

---

## Documentation rule

Every Tier 2+ escalation gets logged in the **Escalation Log** (Notion or dashboard):

| Field | Required |
|---|---|
| Date | Y |
| User name + cohort | Y |
| Tier | Y |
| Issue (1 line) | Y |
| Coach response | Y |
| Resolution | Y |
| Follow-up date | Y |

Founder reviews log weekly.
</file>

<file path="business/07_Marketing/Ad_Creative_Briefs.md">
# Ad Creative Briefs — Meta + Google

3 ad sets to launch with for Cohort 1.

---

## Ad Set 1 — "The Restarter" (Meta)

**Audience:** 25–40, metros (Bengaluru, Hyderabad, Mumbai, Pune, Delhi NCR), interests: fitness, weight loss, gym, yoga, healthy eating, Zomato, Swiggy.

**Objective:** Lead generation (form fill on landing page).

**Hook variants (test 3):**
- A: "Tired of restarting fitness every Monday?"
- B: "You don't need more motivation. You need a smaller plan."
- C: "Indian food. 20-min workouts. WhatsApp accountability. ₹999."

**Body:** "The 21-Day Fitterverse Reset is a WhatsApp-led cohort for busy Indian professionals. Plate method over calorie counting. Daily check-ins, real coach. Top 3 transformations win cash + free next cohort."

**CTA:** "Reserve my seat — ₹999"

**Visual:** Founder face + plate of Indian home food + phone showing WhatsApp coach reply.

**Budget:** ₹500/day, 7 days = ₹3,500

---

## Ad Set 2 — "The Champion" (Meta retargeting)

**Audience:** Anyone who visited fitterverse.in or engaged with our Instagram in last 30 days but didn't convert.

**Hook:**
- "Top 3 transformations in our cohort win ₹10K, ₹5K, ₹2.5K."

**Body:** "Every cohort, three Fitterverse Champions are crowned — judged on consistency, not crash dieting. ₹17,500 prize pool. Cohort starts [date]. 30 seats."

**CTA:** "Join Cohort [N]"

**Visual:** Mock Champion certificates + day-1/day-21 photos (post-cohort 1 we have real photos to use).

**Budget:** ₹250/day, 7 days = ₹1,750

---

## Ad Set 3 — Google Search

**Keyword groups:**
- "online fitness coach India" (high intent)
- "weight loss program India" (medium intent)
- "fitness accountability coach" (high intent)
- "diet plan for office workers" (medium intent)
- "21 day fitness challenge India" (high intent)
- "WhatsApp fitness coach" (high intent, low volume)

**Ad copy variant 1:**
> 21-Day Fitness Reset · ₹999
> WhatsApp coach. Indian food plan. 30 seats only. No app to install.
> Top 3 transformations win cash. Cohort starts [date].

**Ad copy variant 2:**
> Stop Restarting Fitness Every Monday
> Habit-based, WhatsApp-led, ₹999. Built for busy Indian professionals.
> Reserve a seat now.

**Landing page:** Always send to /reset (not homepage). Cohort-specific landing.

**Budget:** ₹400/day, 14 days = ₹5,600

---

## Total Cohort 1 ad spend

| Channel | Spend |
|---|---|
| Meta — cold audience | ₹3,500 |
| Meta — retargeting | ₹1,750 |
| Google Search | ₹5,600 |
| Total | **₹10,850** |

If we acquire 30 paid users at ₹999 with this spend, CAC = ₹362 and revenue = ₹29,970. Break-even on ads. The point of Cohort 1 is data, not profit.

---

## What we measure per ad set

| Metric | Target |
|---|---|
| CTR | ≥ 1.5% |
| Cost per landing page view | ≤ ₹15 |
| Landing page → assessment start | ≥ 25% |
| Assessment start → payment | ≥ 30% |
| Cost per paid user | ≤ ₹400 |

If any ad set blows ₹2,000 with no conversions, kill it. Iterate creative.
</file>

<file path="business/07_Marketing/Email_Sequences.md">
# Email Sequences

Three sequences for v1.

---

## Sequence A — Lead nurture (assessment-started, didn't pay)

Trigger: completed assessment without paying. 4-email flow over 5 days.

**Email 1 — 30 minutes after drop-off**
- Subject: Your 21-Day Reset plan is ready
- Body: Recap their assessment summary, show the personalized output, link back to payment.

**Email 2 — Day 2**
- Subject: One thing about Cohort [N] you should know
- Body: Show the cohort group concept + Champion prize structure. Soft re-pitch.

**Email 3 — Day 4**
- Subject: We close enrolment in 48 hours
- Body: Urgency. Limited seats. Re-link payment.

**Email 4 — Day 5 (last call)**
- Subject: Last 4 seats for Cohort [N]
- Body: Short. Just a link.

If they don't convert: move to "Future Cohort Waitlist" — 1 email per cohort opening.

---

## Sequence B — Cohort welcome (post-payment, pre-Day-1)

Trigger: payment confirmed.

**Email 1 — Immediate**
- Subject: You're in Cohort [N]. Here's what happens next.
- Body: Confirm payment, link assessment (if not done), what to expect, save WhatsApp number.

**Email 2 — T-3 (3 days before Day 1)**
- Subject: Three days till Day 1 — quick prep checklist
- Body: 5-item checklist (clear schedule, get a measuring tape, bookmark workout link, etc.)

**Email 3 — T-1 (day before Day 1)**
- Subject: Tomorrow we start.
- Body: Founder note. Excitement. WhatsApp group invite. "Day 1 photo by 11:59 PM tomorrow."

---

## Sequence C — Post-cohort (after Day 21)

Trigger: cohort completion.

**Email 1 — Day 22**
- Subject: 21 days done. Here's your full report.
- Body: Personalized summary (auto-generated), Champion submission link.

**Email 2 — Day 24 (Champion announcement)**
- Subject: Champions of Cohort [N] — and a thank you
- Body: Already in `03_Champion_Program/Winner_Announcement_Template.md`.

**Email 3 — Day 28**
- Subject: What's next for you (3 paths)
- Body: 
  - Option 1: Join Cohort [N+1] (₹200 graduate discount)
  - Option 2: Plus plan (₹1,499/month, ongoing accountability)
  - Option 3: Take a break (we'll send you a 1-page maintenance plan)

---

## Sender voice

All emails from "[Founder name], Fitterverse" — not from a brand name. Even at scale, founder-voice emails outperform brand emails 2-3x in this kind of program.

## Compliance

- Every email has unsubscribe link in footer
- Cohort completers are auto-enrolled in "Alumni" list (separate from prospect list)
- We do not buy email lists. Ever.
</file>

